Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large pot over medium heat; cook and stir onion, tomato, and carrot until tender, about 10 minutes. Grind peanuts in a blender or food processor until the consistency of peanut butter, avoiding big chunks. Mix peanut butter, beef broth, and peas into onion mixture; bring soup to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in red chile powder. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a skillet; cook and stir potato until crispy and browned, 5 to 10 minutes. Ladle soup into bowls and top with crispy potato and parsley.